### Customer self-service routes (/me/*)
###
### These require a CUSTOMER access token (issued by the customer App
### Client via /auth/customer/verify). The staff authorizer rejects
### customer tokens, and the customer authorizer rejects staff tokens
### — defense in depth on the audience boundary.
###
### Requires: {{baseUrl}} and {{customerAccessToken}} in http-client env.

### GET /me/profile — read your identity + CRM summary
### → 200 { sub, phone, phoneVerified, name, crm }
###    where crm is { totalReservations, totalSpend, lastReservationAt,
###    lastEventDate, lastTableId } or null when there's no ff-clients
###    record for the customer's phone.
GET {{baseUrl}}/me/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}

### Without auth → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/me/profile

### Staff endpoints reject the customer token (audience mismatch) → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
